text.__SUMMARY__: The Kei Island worm snake (Malayotyphlops kraalii ) is a species of snake in the family Typhlopidae.
text.Etymology: The specific name, kraalii, is in honor of Captain P.F. Kraal of the Dutch military in the Moluccas, who assisted the Italian expedition on which the holotype was collected.
text.Geographic range: M. kraalii is found in the Kai Islands of Indonesia.
